bib_record.title: Production of fission-like events after complete and/ or incomplete fusion of 16O with 159Tb and 169Tm at E/A ~6 MeV

free_txt: D.S.N.College, Unnaa
15-UD Pelletron accelerator
100 c.c active volume
Statistical errors of gamma ray counting
Non-uniform thickness of the sample  (<1%)
Spectrometer efficiency determination (<2%)
Dead time of spectrometer      (<10%)
* Fluctuations in the beam current.
* The beam intensity loss as the beam traverses the
target catcher foil assembly.
* The losses of the product nuclei recoiling out of
the target.
15-UD Pelletron accelerator
The beam flux was monitored using an ORTEC
current integrator device by taking into account the
charge collected in the Faraday cup placed behind the
target-catcher foil assembly.
Irradiated for ~8 hrs for each projectile-
target combination.
159Tb foil (99.99%, ~1.8 mg/cm2) prepared by rolling
method.
169Tm (100%, ~0.6 mg/cm2) prepared by vacuum
evaporation technique.
Al-backing (~2 mg/cm2 for Tb sample, ~1.5 mg/cm2 for
Tm sample) served as energy degrader as well as
catcher foils during the irradiation.
Entry approved by Dr.Pushpendra and P.Singh
